Stapleton Roy (Rear), former U.S. ambassador to China, addresses the U.S.-China Think Tank Symposium in Des Moines, Iowa, the United States, on June 12, 2017.Photo:XinhuaIt is crucial for the United States to develop a positive relationship with China, and the diplomatic approach is preferable during that process, former US ambassador to China Stapleton Roy said Thursday."Having a workable relationship with China is more important now than ever before," Roy said at a virtual panel discussion on US-China relations hosted by China Institute, a New York City-based think tank."We need a better way of managing the bilateral relationship than what we have at the moment," he said, noting that diplomacy is vital to forging ahead US-China ties.

